### Test SOS Alert Endpoints

### 1. Create SOS Alert (with location)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/sos
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "latitude": 40.7128,
  "longitude": -74.0060,
  "accuracy": 10,
  "message": "Emergency! Need help immediately!"
}

### 2. Create SOS Alert (without location)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/sos
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "message": "Emergency alert - location unavailable"
}

### 3. Get all SOS alerts for logged-in user
GET http://localhost:5000/api/sos
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Get specific SOS alert by ID
GET http://localhost:5000/api/sos/ALERT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Update SOS alert status (mark as resolved)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/sos/ALERT_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "status": "resolved"
}

### 6. Delete SOS alert
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/sos/ALERT_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

